The paper also involves the study of graphs without certain subgraphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of weighted local generalization suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of bounds and conjectures in graph theory also falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of a different approach in proving the main result suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
